<h2>
    Chum Salmon Migration in Oregon
</h2>
<h3>
    When Do Chum Salmon Run Near Portland?
</h3>
<p>
    Chum salmon typically migrate from the Pacific Ocean into Oregon’s freshwater streams from <strong>late October through December</strong>. This late fall run provides a narrow but productive window for anglers. Water temperatures and river flow are crucial factors influencing their migration.
</p>
<h3>
    Life Cycle and Behavior
</h3>
<p>
    Chum salmon return to the exact stream in which they were born to spawn, completing a journey that often exceeds 1,000 miles. After spawning, chum salmon die, enriching the ecosystem with vital nutrients. Understanding this cycle helps anglers plan the best times to fish and appreciate the biological significance of their catch.
</p>
