<h2>
    Best Time to Fish for Chum Salmon
</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Peak Months</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    The <strong>peak season</strong> for chum salmon fishing near Portland is <strong>mid-November to early December</strong>. This window coincides with increased river flows from fall rains, which signal the salmon to begin their spawning run.
</p>
<h3>
    Weather and Water Conditions
</h3>
<p>
    Chum prefer <strong>cooler water temperatures (45°F to 55°F)</strong> and moderate river flows. Avoid fishing immediately after heavy rains when water is too murky or fast-moving. Ideal conditions include <strong>slightly rising river levels</strong> and <strong>good water clarity</strong>.
</p>
<h2>
